intro: Brachyscome dalbyensis, commonly known as the Dalby daisy, is a flowering plant native to Queensland, Australia. It belongs to the Asteraceae family and is characterized by its small, daisy-like flowers with white petals and a yellow center. The plant typically grows in open, sunny habitats such as grasslands and rocky areas. It has hairy stems and leaves, which help it retain moisture in its arid environment. Brachyscome dalbyensis is also noted for its ornamental value and is sometimes cultivated in gardens.
